''[[Law & Order: Special Victims Unit]]'', a spin-off of the crime drama ''[[Law & Order]]'', follows the detectives who work in the "Special Victims Unit" of the 16th District [[New York City Police Department]]'s, a unit that focuses on crimes involving [[rape]], [[sexual assault]] and [[child molestation]], as well as any crime loosely connected with any of the three, such as [[domestic violence]], [[kidnapping]] and [[child abandonment]]. Since its debut in September 1999, the series has generally shown four detectives working the unit, though at times, five, under the leadership of Captain [[Donald Cragen]]. The unit also has a prosecutor assigned from the DA's office, and frequently interacts with specific medical examiners and the unit's psychiatrist [[George Huang (Law & Order)|George Huang]].
